00:36:20,920 --> 00:36:27,820
So after a year of praying five times a day, fasting the month of Ramadan, following God's

478
00:36:27,820 --> 00:36:29,420
law, you still have problems.

479
00:36:31,380 --> 00:36:33,440
Then you say, what is this? I came to

480
00:36:33,960 --> 00:36:35,699
God because I want

481
00:36:35,699 --> 00:36:37,159
to be happy. How come I have problems?

482
00:36:39,260 --> 00:36:39,699
Then

483
00:36:39,699 --> 00:36:40,760
you see, you're not a Muslim.

484
00:36:41,400 --> 00:36:43,400
You didn't come to God. You're coming to happiness.

485
00:36:45,639 --> 00:36:47,440
You must be proven

486
00:36:47,960 --> 00:36:48,679
that you

487
00:36:48,679 --> 00:36:51,579
know that God is the Master.

488
00:36:51,739 --> 00:36:53,320
It doesn't matter what happens to you.

489
00:36:53,519 --> 00:36:55,420
Happiness or misery or accidents.

490
00:36:55,800 --> 00:36:56,420
You're coming to God.

491
00:36:56,420 --> 00:37:04,960
What I mean is, it's a knowledge that is established in your mind, a conviction, that it doesn't matter what happens, it's not going to change.

492
00:37:05,559 --> 00:37:13,860
Therefore, you must be proven, you must be shown that you have reached that conviction, and that is proven by steadfastness.

493
00:37:14,159 --> 00:37:24,460
Steadfastness is very important. It may take 15 years, it may take 20 years, until you attain that steadfastness, it may take 2 months.

494
00:37:25,739 --> 00:37:28,280
But the state of perfect happiness is not the object.

495
00:37:30,000 --> 00:37:34,659
The object is belief in God, knowing that God is the Master.

496
00:37:35,579 --> 00:37:38,179
In fact, when you say, why is this happening to me?

497
00:37:38,619 --> 00:37:41,019
You're not a Muslim, you're not submissive, you're objecting.

498
00:37:42,079 --> 00:37:43,019
You are objecting.

499
00:37:43,719 --> 00:37:47,380
You're not a Muslim yet, and you don't deserve the perfect happiness.

500
00:37:48,000 --> 00:37:49,199
Where there are no problems.

501
00:37:50,920 --> 00:37:52,659
When you say, why is this happening to me?

502
00:37:52,659 --> 00:37:53,880
I prayed my five prayers.

503
00:37:55,079 --> 00:37:58,519
Because you haven't come to God, you have come to happiness.

504
00:37:58,679 --> 00:37:59,539
This is your objective.

505
00:38:00,539 --> 00:38:07,400
You want a life without any problems, so this is what you want, and this is what you're

506
00:38:07,400 --> 00:38:07,619
worshipping.

507
00:38:10,460 --> 00:38:12,199
Now, what are the choices?

508
00:38:13,800 --> 00:38:18,820
You can be steadfast for 15 years, and then you attain the perfect conviction, the perfect

509
00:38:19,300 --> 00:38:21,340
happiness that comes as a bonus, you see.

510
00:38:22,659 --> 00:38:25,000
That's something on the side, not an objective.

511
00:38:25,980 --> 00:38:31,760
It will come as a natural consequence, and you will be convicted that God is the only Master.

512
00:38:32,800 --> 00:38:39,340
The other choice is to have, say, 15 years of misery, and then go on.

513
00:38:40,639 --> 00:38:45,119
In other words, you be steadfast for 15 years and then attain perfect happiness,

514
00:38:45,380 --> 00:38:50,199
or have the 15 years of misery plus eternal misery. That's the other choice.

515
00:38:52,880 --> 00:38:54,659
There is no other choice.

516
00:38:57,400 --> 00:38:58,880
So, steadfastness is very important.

517
00:38:59,179 --> 00:39:01,340
Seek help through steadfastness.

518
00:39:01,400 --> 00:39:03,300
You are steadfast. You are unshakable.

519
00:39:03,480 --> 00:39:04,460
It doesn't matter what happens.

520
00:39:05,800 --> 00:39:06,599
Something happens to you.

521
00:39:06,699 --> 00:39:08,539
Why did this happen to you? I'm not going to pray today.

522
00:39:08,900 --> 00:39:10,800
It's cutting your losses. Why do you pray?

523
00:39:13,699 --> 00:39:17,780
When you are convinced, nothing is going to change that knowledge.

524
00:39:18,979 --> 00:39:19,860
Okay, question's good.

525
00:39:19,940 --> 00:39:20,280
Very good.

526
00:39:21,959 --> 00:39:25,480
I was going to say, I was trying to think about the other thing.

527
00:39:26,199 --> 00:39:29,059
I was trying to think about the other thing.

528
00:39:29,340 --> 00:39:32,059
Sometimes, you know, we can talk about, I know when we disobey God,

529
00:39:32,159 --> 00:39:33,099
we all act like a kid,

530
00:39:33,559 --> 00:39:36,480
but I remember our first time seeing a child trying to get drunk,

531
00:39:36,519 --> 00:39:39,860
I would say, I don't think there's anything tempting in that,

532
00:39:40,239 --> 00:39:42,000
the first time that we did that,

533
00:39:42,000 --> 00:39:43,179
you know, we all had a gift,

534
00:39:43,420 --> 00:39:44,559
and we were told, you know, "Take care of that."

535
00:39:49,260 --> 00:39:54,199
That's why the verses of the test came immediately after steadfastness.

536
00:39:55,360 --> 00:40:01,480
Because God wants you to show the angels and to show Satan that you are convinced that He is the only Master,

537
00:40:01,599 --> 00:40:03,860
and nothing is going to change that no matter what happens.

538
00:40:04,860 --> 00:40:09,820
Extreme success, extreme failure, death, sickness, death of a world.

539
00:40:27,419 --> 00:40:35,360
But then, it was like, I know, if I miss the Quran study, if I miss a beat, but then...

540
00:40:35,360 --> 00:40:39,800
still, what I'm trying to say is, you don't want to, you don't want to, you don't want to.

541
00:40:39,800 --> 00:40:46,239
I went through a 15-year test, and again, not submitting, but that same test was like a 40-year test.

542
00:40:46,239 --> 00:40:47,900
So is that going to take you around the world?

543
00:40:48,019 --> 00:40:54,159
You know, like if you think, "Oh wow, this happened, so then, okay, I'm in this test."

544
00:40:54,159 --> 00:40:59,800
The test, in your case, was being far away without transportation. That's the test.

545
00:41:00,639 --> 00:41:06,139
Now, so you have to struggle, you have to go around and find a ride and do what you can.

546
00:41:06,139 --> 00:41:11,059
You have to do your best to go to the Quran study.

547
00:41:12,400 --> 00:41:13,760
That's what you're supposed to do.

548
00:41:13,840 --> 00:41:17,599
But then, if you can't find a ride, and there is no way you can make it,

549
00:41:18,420 --> 00:41:22,159
then you satisfy the requirement, and then you submit to that.

550
00:41:22,679 --> 00:41:24,019
You have to submit.

551
00:41:25,179 --> 00:41:28,539
After you do what you're supposed to do, after you do your best,

552
00:41:29,139 --> 00:41:32,880
and you cannot accomplish it, then you submit.

553
00:41:33,099 --> 00:41:33,780
You don't object.

554
00:41:35,079 --> 00:41:36,800
Some of us do a lot of this.

555
00:41:37,199 --> 00:41:38,400
I get, I get students.

556
00:41:39,480 --> 00:41:42,860
I always remember when I was teaching the young men and women,

557
00:41:42,880 --> 00:41:45,320
the emotions involved are intense.

558
00:41:46,260 --> 00:41:48,559
And I think this is the case when I talk to a student,

559
00:41:48,679 --> 00:41:52,119
and I notice that there are other students who have the same feeling.

560
00:41:52,239 --> 00:41:54,659
But something that kind of surprises me,

561
00:41:54,780 --> 00:41:57,079
because I'm not the same kind of guy as probably other students,

562
00:41:57,320 --> 00:41:59,519
is that I'm past that age, and they say,

563
00:42:00,579 --> 00:42:07,699
"Well, you know, we don't have jobs, and we need more money, we need more money, we need more money."

564
00:42:07,960 --> 00:42:11,320
"So a ton of money would be okay, but we don't have a lot."

565
00:42:11,460 --> 00:42:13,119
We are told we should be patient, because it's good.

566
00:42:13,519 --> 00:42:15,940
But sometimes it's really difficult.

567
00:42:16,099 --> 00:42:17,059
It's a challenge.

568
00:42:17,340 --> 00:42:20,500
You want your reward, but you didn't even work.

569
00:42:20,619 --> 00:42:21,739
God is good for everything.

570
00:42:22,960 --> 00:42:25,920
I even have to say that I'm happy that I've read this.

571
00:42:25,920 --> 00:42:35,039
because I didn't get it before. But my faith didn't get worse because I didn't get it. My faith didn't get worse. And on the opposite, I think it's...

572
00:42:35,519 --> 00:42:42,619
The teachings of the Quran, the meaning of the Quran will come to you at the right time, when you read it, at the time you need it.

573
00:42:42,820 --> 00:42:48,119
It's like, you know, the Quran is never a boring book, but every time you read it, you get something new out of it.

574
00:42:48,900 --> 00:42:52,179
And you say, "I've read this a million times, how come I never saw this before?"

575
00:42:52,179 --> 00:42:53,840
Yes, yes. Because you were not ready for it.

576
00:42:55,019 --> 00:43:03,300
But, but, you know, it's so important that I think that this is a, the real realization that needs to be achieved, I think.

577
00:43:04,239 --> 00:43:12,320
The lesson that many of you would learn to see, perhaps, is how you relate it to your real life.

578
00:43:16,120 --> 00:43:30,500
I think if you step back, you will see it's a good thing, that God trains in you certain qualities, some of the qualities you need.

579
00:43:31,099 --> 00:43:35,340
For example, you can find yourself with a lack of wealth.

580
00:43:36,039 --> 00:43:38,880
When you eat or drink, it's always sparse.

581
00:43:39,179 --> 00:43:41,019
You can, you know, count the food.

582
00:43:41,679 --> 00:43:47,559
And, uh, if you have, uh, a child, or if, you know, you could not have a child,

583
00:43:48,019 --> 00:43:51,239
or if you're given a child, and then this child is taken from you,

584
00:43:51,300 --> 00:43:53,659
then you are tried, and then you get your reward.

585
00:43:54,439 --> 00:43:58,800
Or things like this, you know, and, uh...

586
00:43:58,800 --> 00:44:01,480
And when you're successful, you're rewarded for it, that's all.

587
00:44:02,159 --> 00:44:06,619
But the idea is, I'll give you a good example.

588
00:44:06,840 --> 00:44:09,800
When you were young, you probably did this, I did this.

589
00:44:10,019 --> 00:44:13,440
When you were young and not quite sure of your religion,

590
00:44:14,639 --> 00:44:17,320
you know how the examination periods are really tough,

591
00:44:17,420 --> 00:44:18,900
you know, they really make you pray to God.

592
00:44:19,320 --> 00:44:22,400
And I noticed that I and my friends were more religious

593
00:44:22,400 --> 00:44:24,579
during examinations than at other times.

594
00:44:26,400 --> 00:44:31,500
You know, when you don't need God, you know, you don't pray as much, you're not as religious

595
00:44:31,500 --> 00:44:31,900
or receptive.

596
00:44:32,659 --> 00:44:36,699
But when you're in a squeeze, then you turn to God.

597
00:44:36,960 --> 00:44:40,900
So, God says, you must be steadfast under all circumstances.

598
00:44:41,480 --> 00:44:45,579
And we get an example in the Quran where people are riding a ship, and a storm comes,

599
00:44:46,199 --> 00:44:49,699
and they're about to drown, and then they turn to God.

600
00:44:49,840 --> 00:44:51,099
But here's what happens when they reach the shore.

601
00:44:51,320 --> 00:44:53,599
As soon as they land safely, they forget God.

602
00:44:54,759 --> 00:45:09,280
That's not steadfastness. Steadfastness means to think of God on the ocean, on the land, whether traveling or at home, in stormy conditions or in peaceful conditions.

603
00:45:09,699 --> 00:45:12,519
Excuse me, we need to remember something that you said last week, too.

604
00:45:18,719 --> 00:45:20,320
I think you need to remember

605
00:45:20,320 --> 00:45:26,639
that the test is coming in difficult because you said about

606
00:45:26,639 --> 00:45:29,840
you can't do this, you can't do that, so now you're thinking about

607
00:45:29,840 --> 00:45:32,699
what you could use to do this test.

608
00:45:32,719 --> 00:45:35,179
I think you need to remember that.

609
00:45:41,079 --> 00:45:47,139
Yes. Everything you said. As long as the sun comes up and you can see it, you're still alive.

610
00:45:47,500 --> 00:45:53,639
There are many things you have to think about. How much do you pay for this?

611
00:45:54,960 --> 00:46:04,960
We give that great price, as we're doing by the way, and many times we waver after.

612
00:46:05,539 --> 00:46:10,900
I think this thing about how easily we forget is, I think, very, very normal.

613
00:46:11,539 --> 00:46:12,739
It should not be normal.

614
00:46:13,239 --> 00:46:14,880
Like, this is what happens.

615
00:46:15,519 --> 00:46:18,760
Allah, I want this letter, let's say, from my mother.

616
00:46:18,920 --> 00:46:21,880
And every day you're missing it, praying, "Allah, I want this letter."

617
00:46:21,880 --> 00:46:26,300
And after waiting three or four weeks, the mailman comes with the letter.

618
00:46:26,840 --> 00:46:32,880
And when you see it, you forget Allah. You thank the mailman, you give him a tip,

619
00:46:33,099 --> 00:46:39,480
and after reading the letter, then you realize you have thanked everybody except Allah.

620
00:46:41,320 --> 00:46:43,119
It's very common.

621
00:46:43,119 --> 00:46:43,300
No problem.

622
00:46:44,220 --> 00:46:47,900
You have to also seek help through steadfastness and Salat.

623
00:46:49,119 --> 00:46:53,599
If you are steadfast and you do your Salat, you're going to receive help.

624
00:47:13,119 --> 00:47:13,219
Right.

625
00:47:19,599 --> 00:47:22,500
and in 2:156,

626
00:47:22,500 --> 00:47:27,380
when a disaster strikes them, they say, "We belong to God, and to Him we are returning."

627
00:47:27,940 --> 00:47:32,059
So ultimately, in other words, the submitters say, "What does God want with me?"

628
00:47:41,639 --> 00:47:49,059
When I got in trouble in Libya, and they threw me in the dungeon, I was very upset. I was

629
00:47:49,059 --> 00:47:51,219
objecting for a couple of days.

630
00:47:52,960 --> 00:47:55,039
Why, why, why did this happen to me?

631
00:47:56,800 --> 00:48:05,639
And then I was, I didn't read any books, nothing. I was afraid I would forget the Quran, I was reading it continuously.

632
00:48:06,420 --> 00:48:08,179
And then I came to a verse that said,

633
00:48:12,300 --> 00:48:18,559
I was objecting violently, then I totally submitted.

634
00:48:20,699 --> 00:48:22,699
You know, this is what God wants us to do.

635
00:48:22,800 --> 00:48:23,940
This is what this verse means.

636
00:48:24,340 --> 00:48:26,579
When it says that we belong to God, I said,

637
00:48:26,639 --> 00:48:28,440
"Well, this is what God wants to do with me.

638
00:48:28,619 --> 00:48:30,119
There's nothing anybody can do."

639
00:48:31,179 --> 00:48:32,699
That's why you just have to accept it.

640
00:48:33,239 --> 00:48:37,559
Okay, that's when I was talking about the first song to hear.

641
00:48:38,559 --> 00:48:40,800
That's when I was talking about the first song to hear.

642
00:48:40,820 --> 00:48:41,280
Is that okay?

643
00:48:41,679 --> 00:48:42,000
No.

644
00:48:42,039 --> 00:48:42,860
Okay, that first song.

645
00:48:43,219 --> 00:48:44,460
I know it's not okay,

646
00:48:44,480 --> 00:48:47,179
because we should keep that second song to sing with you.

647
00:48:47,179 --> 00:48:53,239
But it was okay for us, us being human, to hang our heads for a while, as long as we could get back as quickly as we possibly could.

648
00:48:53,440 --> 00:48:53,760
Right.

649
00:48:53,760 --> 00:48:54,599
That was the second part.

650
00:48:54,840 --> 00:48:56,659
It was the Quran that reminded me.

651
00:48:56,840 --> 00:48:57,400
Okay, okay.

652
00:48:57,480 --> 00:48:58,460
So that's what I was coming on to.

653
00:48:58,460 --> 00:48:58,780
Thank God.

654
00:48:59,739 --> 00:50:03,360
But that was the toughest test that I ever had in my life.

655
00:49:03,619 --> 00:49:06,699
That was really, that was the toughest test.

656
00:49:07,519 --> 00:49:10,019
But the rewards were beautiful after that.

657
00:49:13,059 --> 00:49:35,940
And then just two days later, I was really honored. You know, the order from the president came and they kicked the doors, they beat up the jailers, and they had me in a government limousine and brought me into the, what they call, the People's Palace, where the second man in the country was.

658
00:49:35,940 --> 00:49:43,619
The bodyguard gave me a big hug and asked me what happened, and he is the one who put me in.

659
00:49:46,279 --> 00:49:48,460
They pretended like they rescued me.

660
00:49:48,639 --> 00:49:50,880
But God was doing the whole thing.

661
00:49:51,019 --> 00:49:57,519
But only after I submitted, and I had said this, and then this verse, I identified with this verse right away,

662
00:49:58,099 --> 00:50:04,860
2:156. Look at it. If a disaster strikes them—to me that was the biggest disaster ever.

663
00:50:05,800 --> 00:50:11,099
Because it's a place where there are no laws, there are no courts. They don't have to put you on trial any time.

664
00:50:11,360 --> 00:50:15,280
They don't have to release you. They don't have to justify or give you any reason.

665
00:50:15,460 --> 00:50:21,900
You don't know what will happen to you. And on the walls of the dungeon I saw those lines marking days and weeks.

666
00:50:21,900 --> 00:50:26,039
People would put a cross each week, you know, and I didn't know how long they...

667
00:50:27,779 --> 00:50:31,380
Yeah, really, I thought I'd never see my children again.

668
00:50:32,280 --> 00:50:39,239
And it happened before. I mean, they took Imam Musa al-Sadr of Lebanon, and he disappeared.

669
00:50:39,480 --> 00:50:40,239
He never came back again.

670
00:50:41,300 --> 00:50:42,960
There's lots of speculation what happened to him.

671
00:50:43,559 --> 00:50:50,679
Also, I know from experience that when they do this to you, even for one hour, you become an enemy of the state.

672
00:50:51,380 --> 00:50:54,860
They won't let you go out to speak of the barbaric treatment against them.

673
00:50:55,579 --> 00:51:04,119
The barbaric treatment and the barbaric cruelty in the dungeon and all the horrible things that happen to human beings over there.

674
00:51:04,599 --> 00:51:09,119
They won't let you go. But it was no less than a miracle.

675
00:51:10,039 --> 00:51:12,099
Yet it's very easy for God to do it.

676
00:51:12,800 --> 00:51:15,019
So when we look at this verse again, 2:156.

677
00:51:15,019 --> 00:51:21,599
When a disaster strikes them, they say, "We belong to God, and to Him we will return."

678
00:51:22,820 --> 00:51:29,920
So this is exactly what I said by instinct. Alhamdulillah, all I said was, when God wants to do for me,

679
00:51:31,320 --> 00:51:35,579
who's going to do anything about it? And I had a great sense of relief.

680
00:51:35,780 --> 00:51:40,179
And only then I can imagine the angels working on my release.

681
00:51:40,839 --> 00:51:45,179
They go and work on the people and make them make this rash decision of letting me go?

682
00:51:45,440 --> 00:51:45,980
Unheard of.

683
00:51:49,139 --> 00:51:51,739
Really, unheard of. I haven't seen anybody go in and come out.

684
00:51:55,199 --> 00:51:55,599
Yeah?

685
00:51:55,599 --> 00:51:55,679
Yeah?

686
00:52:07,679 --> 00:52:08,619
The objection?

687
00:52:11,200 --> 00:52:14,280
The objection is simply lack of faith in God.

688
00:52:15,840 --> 00:52:18,019
When I was put in that disaster,

689
00:52:19,079 --> 00:52:20,539
I just complained.

690
00:52:21,000 --> 00:52:21,840
I forgot.

691
00:52:22,159 --> 00:52:23,880
My faith in God was not strong.

692
00:52:24,460 --> 00:52:29,599
I was objecting to the test. I was thinking, why is this happening to me?

693
00:52:31,099 --> 00:52:36,139
That shouldn't happen to me. That was objection. That was bad.

694
00:52:36,239 --> 00:52:39,119
Because for as long as I was flunking the test, I was in bad shape.

695
00:52:41,699 --> 00:52:45,480
But when I made that statement, we belong to God and He can do anything with us,

696
00:52:45,739 --> 00:52:51,219
I will submit. Then everything, the test was over. There was no point in continuing the test.

697
00:52:52,000 --> 00:52:55,400
But had I continued with that attitude, why is this happening to me?

698
00:52:56,400 --> 00:52:57,800
I would have remained there.

699
00:53:05,059 --> 00:53:08,219
Okay, our next picture is Adam Baruni, he's getting up now.

700
00:53:11,719 --> 00:53:13,440
Adam, want to take the Hajj pilgrimage?

701
00:53:16,099 --> 00:53:17,920
Inga, why don't you take the Hajj pilgrimage?

702
00:53:17,920 --> 00:53:20,880
This is the Adam, not the one I was talking about.

703
00:53:22,099 --> 00:53:24,099
He's getting up. When did he stop getting up?

704
00:53:26,659 --> 00:53:27,960
Huh? A couple of days?

705
00:53:28,820 --> 00:53:29,460
Masha'Allah.

706
00:53:29,719 --> 00:53:33,699
He's busy, you know. He's sitting there eating food, drinks and so on.

707
00:53:34,219 --> 00:53:36,400
Throwing them up in the air and chewing on them.

708
00:53:37,280 --> 00:53:38,659
He's having fun. Masha'Allah.

709
00:53:41,380 --> 00:53:41,800
Okay.

710
00:53:42,840 --> 00:53:48,320
Indeed, Safa and Marwah are among the rites of God.

711
00:53:48,980 --> 00:53:56,500
So anyone who observes Hajj or `Umrah commits no error by traversing the distance between them.

712
00:53:57,559 --> 00:54:02,920
If one volunteers to do more, then God is Appreciative, Omniscient.

713
00:54:03,500 --> 00:54:07,559
As for those who conceal the revelations we send down, and the guidance,

714
00:54:09,880 --> 00:54:14,059
after We have made them clear for the people in the scripture,

715
00:54:14,619 --> 00:54:18,739
Except for those who repent, reform, and proclaim; I will redeem them.

716
00:54:18,940 --> 00:54:20,980
I am the Redeemer, the Most Merciful.

717
00:54:21,420 --> 00:54:26,820
Those who disbelieve, and die as disbelievers, upon them is the curse of God,

718
00:54:26,820 --> 00:54:27,860
and the angels, and all the people.

719
00:54:28,539 --> 00:54:30,500
They abide therein forever.

720
00:54:30,579 --> 00:54:33,500
The retribution is never commuted for them, nor are they respited.

721
00:54:34,019 --> 00:54:35,679
Your god is one god.

722
00:54:35,679 --> 00:54:39,579
There is no god except He, the Most Gracious, Most Merciful.

723
00:54:41,720 --> 00:54:43,980
The pagans had idols on Safa and Marwah,

724
00:54:46,200 --> 00:54:48,980
and the Muslims had something against walking

725
00:54:49,680 --> 00:54:52,139
between them. No, no.

726
00:54:52,199 --> 00:54:57,500
Okay, I see. Hajj, like all worships in Islam,

727
00:54:58,559 --> 00:55:00,559
came through Ibrahim.

728
00:55:02,799 --> 00:55:10,380
And Safa and Marwah are two mounds where Hagar used to go up them to look and see when Ibrahim was coming.

729
00:55:10,579 --> 00:55:13,260
Because he left them there, he left Hagar and Ishmael there.

730
00:55:13,900 --> 00:55:20,539
And he'd go to Sarah in Palestine for a couple of months, and come to Hagar and Ishmael for a couple of months.

731
00:55:21,320 --> 00:55:26,800
So she used to go up, and they were really in distress just before the discovery of water.

732
00:55:27,639 --> 00:55:31,119
So she would go up and look for Ibrahim, and then go to this one,

733
00:55:31,619 --> 00:55:35,119
because he came with the supplies. The supplies were running down.

734
00:55:36,239 --> 00:55:40,360
And then the well of Zamzam sprung out from the earth.

735
00:55:40,719 --> 00:55:46,639
And then caravans would stop and buy the water from them, and they became rich, etc., etc.

736
00:55:46,860 --> 00:55:52,440
So, this is a commemoration of the fact that God will take care of you.

737
00:55:53,380 --> 00:56:01,760
So some people just can't imagine that God will provide for you when you never expect.

738
00:56:02,159 --> 00:56:09,619
When you put your trust in God, the verse says those who fear God will be provided for

739
00:56:09,619 --> 00:56:12,920
when they never expect. And some people just can't imagine that.

740
00:56:13,199 --> 00:56:18,579
So this symbolizes the fact that Ibrahim followed the instructions.

741
00:56:19,059 --> 00:56:24,079
He took Hagar and Ishmael and put them in a barren desert, no plants, no water, nothing,

742
00:56:24,300 --> 00:56:26,460
and said, "You're going to live here."

743
00:56:27,320 --> 00:56:29,519
Can you imagine going in the middle of the desert?

744
00:56:29,659 --> 00:56:31,900
Not like the desert where I'm going here.

745
00:56:32,099 --> 00:56:37,400
If you've seen the desert in Yuma, between Yuma and El Centro, where it is just yellow sand dunes,

746
00:56:37,400 --> 00:56:38,760
this is how Mecca looked.

747
00:56:40,099 --> 00:56:42,019
And there were no plants, nothing, no water.

748
00:56:42,920 --> 00:56:47,480
And this is the area that, as you see in other verses in Quran,

749
00:56:49,299 --> 00:56:53,599
"I have settled part of my family in a plantless valley near your sacred house."

750
00:56:54,300 --> 00:56:55,219
He left them.

751
00:56:55,900 --> 00:56:57,119
He left them with some supplies.

752
00:56:57,360 --> 00:56:59,159
This is the lesson that God selected for you.

753
00:56:59,280 --> 00:56:59,500
Why?

754
00:56:59,800 --> 00:57:04,239
Because God provided for them.

755
00:57:04,280 --> 00:57:05,019
The water came out.

756
00:57:05,179 --> 00:57:06,179
The caravans came.

757
00:57:06,320 --> 00:57:07,039
The support really came.

758
00:57:08,260 --> 00:57:08,699
With it.

759
00:57:10,000 --> 00:57:11,199
God provided for them.

760
00:57:12,139 --> 00:57:15,559
So, this Safa and Marwah business is a commemoration of that.

761
00:57:16,460 --> 00:57:21,039
And it reminds you that God will provide for you and take care of you. He guarantees that.

762
00:57:23,199 --> 00:57:26,199
When God says, "I guarantee you provision in this life," guaranteed.

763
00:57:27,139 --> 00:57:29,239
All I want you to do is worship Me alone.

764
00:57:31,280 --> 00:57:35,599
I'm going to take care of all your needs, and I just want you to make a decision.

765
00:57:36,480 --> 00:57:37,480
Worship Me alone.

766
00:57:39,179 --> 00:57:42,019
So, Safa and Marwah have the symbol for you.

767
00:57:44,619 --> 00:57:47,360
The verse says: "Whoever volunteers good, God is Appreciative, Aware."

768
00:57:47,559 --> 00:57:51,940
Right, what is this now?

769
00:57:52,119 --> 00:57:53,679
I have the verse here, and I want you to see it.

770
00:57:54,820 --> 00:57:57,159
Let's go further to it to see it. I can see it.

771
00:57:57,159 --> 00:57:59,599
It's bringing it to like modern day times.

772
00:58:00,279 --> 00:58:03,380
Right, because it's traversing the distance seven times.

773
00:58:06,079 --> 00:58:10,099
So, but if you want to do it more, if you want to commemorate, because you commemorate God.

774
00:58:10,099 --> 00:58:14,619
You say, "Allah is the greatest," all the time you are going back and forth, you are saying that.

775
00:58:14,820 --> 00:58:17,039
You are saying, لَبَيْكَ اللَّهُمَّ لَبَيْكَ

776
00:58:17,039 --> 00:58:21,119
It means, "I respond to you, my Lord, and I obey your commandments."

777
00:58:23,480 --> 00:58:28,659
It's a big thing, so it says that if you volunteer more of this worship,

778
00:58:29,199 --> 00:58:30,800
then you will be rewarded for it.

779
00:58:34,460 --> 00:58:36,039
لَبَيْكَ اللَّهُمَّ لَبَيْكَ

780
00:58:36,780 --> 00:58:41,500
Labbayk is an expression, like when a king calls a slave.

781
00:58:43,960 --> 00:58:46,039
When the slave comes and says, "Labbayk."

782
00:58:46,900 --> 00:58:48,280
It means, "At Your command."

783
00:58:49,539 --> 00:58:50,699
Literally, "At Your command."

784
00:58:52,380 --> 00:58:55,159
So you say that when you make the Hajj,

785
00:58:55,340 --> 00:58:56,659
you always have to say that.

786
00:58:56,800 --> 00:59:01,119
Labbayk Allahumma: "My God, Our God, I am Your slave."

787
00:59:02,460 --> 00:59:04,139
You called me, and here I am.

788
00:59:06,299 --> 00:59:11,000
I am truthful in my absolute obedience to You.

789
00:59:12,780 --> 00:59:13,659
Beautiful words, yeah.

790
00:59:16,179 --> 00:59:17,820
Yes. But this is what it says here.

791
00:59:21,599 --> 00:59:22,739
Yeah, and you are told already.

792
00:59:28,019 --> 00:59:31,559
Yes, but in other words, you are not to think of idols by doing this.

793
00:59:32,480 --> 00:59:38,760
You are doing it because of My command. In other words, some people say if you're going around the Ka'bah, then the Ka'bah is your idol.

794
00:59:38,980 --> 00:59:44,179
It was only because of that. It's like God telling the angels to fall prostrate before Adam.

795
00:59:45,960 --> 00:59:58,960
But it wasn't for Adam; it was obeying the commandment of God who said it's okay to go around or traverse the distance between them.

796
00:59:59,719 --> 01:00:03,500
And in this way, you are not idolizing the Ka'bah or idolizing Safa and Marwah.

797
01:00:04,380 --> 01:00:06,139
Because it is a commandment from God.

798
01:00:07,599 --> 01:00:12,119
Now, you see, God was telling us it's alright; the contrast is with Adam. It's okay, "I am telling you."

799
01:00:15,259 --> 01:00:17,119
Yes, "I'm telling you."

800
01:00:19,760 --> 01:00:23,320
And for voluntary worship, there is more reward.

801
01:00:25,000 --> 01:00:29,760
Because these are authorized practices.

802
01:00:31,000 --> 01:00:33,179
While we are on this subject, I must say that

803
01:00:33,179 --> 01:00:36,440
all pillars of Submission are shown in this surah

804
01:00:36,440 --> 01:00:38,039
in the sequence of the year.

805
01:00:38,460 --> 01:00:40,800
The first one was the Salat and then the Ka'bah,

806
01:00:41,300 --> 01:00:44,400
and then comes the fasting in the ninth month,

807
01:00:44,539 --> 01:00:46,920
and now this is Hajj in the twelfth month.

808
01:00:49,340 --> 01:00:54,360
So, you remember when we went through the fasting verses, do you remember? Yeah?

809
01:00:55,579 --> 01:00:58,699
No, not fasting. It's next to...

810
01:00:58,699 --> 01:00:59,019
Oh, is it?

811
01:01:01,679 --> 01:01:03,400
Oh, oops. This is an oops.

812
01:01:05,400 --> 01:01:09,239
So, I think the Hajj, yeah, Hajj comes after the fasting.

813
01:01:09,320 --> 01:01:10,400
When you make the Hajj after.

814
01:01:10,639 --> 01:01:10,900
Right.

815
01:01:10,940 --> 01:01:15,460
So, this has to do with the Safa and Marwah.

816
01:01:15,460 --> 01:01:15,920
Yeah.

817
01:01:17,219 --> 01:01:18,980
Because Behrouz is not here, right?

818
01:01:19,320 --> 01:01:21,280
Behrouz is not here.

819
01:01:21,820 --> 01:01:22,300
Yeah.

820
01:01:22,760 --> 01:01:22,940
Yeah.

821
01:01:23,860 --> 01:01:24,340
Yeah.

822
01:01:24,559 --> 01:01:24,619
Yeah.

823
01:01:24,619 --> 01:01:24,719
Yeah.

824
01:01:25,179 --> 01:01:25,659
Yeah.

825
